com.broudy.gcm.boundary.enhanced.fxmlrelated

Class EnhancedFXMLController

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.broudy.gcm.boundary.enhanced.fxmlrelated.EnhancedFXMLController
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ClientInitializingController, CustomerCatalogBrowserController, CustomerCityExplorerController, CustomerSidePaneController, EmployeeCitiesEditorController, EmployeeCityExplorerController, EmployeeMapsEditorController, EmployeeMyAccountController, EmployeeMyWorkspaceController, EmployeeRequestsViewerController, EmployeeSidePaneController, JustBrowseSidePaneController, MainContainerController, NotificationsController, SignInFormController, SignUpForm1Controller, SignUpForm2Controller, SignUpForm3Controller, WelcomeScreenController 

    public abstract class EnhancedFXMLController
extends java.lang.Object
    This controller provides an option to link and unlink it from program's current flow. It also provides an option to initialize it one-time when it is loaded for the first time in case it is a singleton.

    Created on the 1st of September, 2019.

    Author:
    Julian Broudy

    • Method Detail

      • initializeEnhancedController

        public abstract void initializeEnhancedController()
        All the one-time initializations should be implemented in this method.

      • link

        final void link()
        This method is called by the EnhancedFXMLLoader after all previous-interconnected controllers have been constructed, injected & activated. This method activates the controller IFF the controller is NOT currently activate.

      • unlink

        final void unlink()
        This method should be used in order to "suspend" an EnhancedFXMLController if needed.

        For example:
        In some occasions, switching between controllers might require unbinding some of the first controller's controls or removing some of its Listeners.

      • activateController

        protected abstract void activateController()
        This method should implement all the steps that turn an initialized & "unlinked" controller into a "linked" one.

        By default this method calls activateValidators(), activateListeners() ()}, activateListeners() ()} and activateEventHandlers() ()} in this order.

      • deactivateController

        protected abstract void deactivateController()
        This method should implement all the steps that turn a "linked" controller into an "unlinked" one.
